    <div class="cc_row">
      <div class="headline">
        <h1>Using Downloaded Models with Gazebo</h1>
      </div>
      <p>The contents of a downloaded model must be placed in a location that Gazebo can find. The following steps assume you're using Linux. </p>
      <ol>
        <li>Download a model</li>
        <li><tt>$ tar xvf &lt;path_to_model&gt; -C ~/.gazebo/models</tt></li>
        <li><tt>$ gazebo</tt></li>
        <li>Select the Insert tab in Gazebo</li>
        <li>Select the model, and click in the main window.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="span6">
  	<div class="cc_row">
      <div class="contributing_row">
      <div class="headline">
        <h1>Contributing Models</h1>
        <p> We encourage you to give back to the community by uploading your own models. We kindly ask that you adhere to the following guidelines:
        </p>

      <ul class="guidelines">
        <li>Only upload models if you are the creator, or have obtained the explicit approval of the creator to upload the model."
        <li> All materials will be licensed under <a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/" target="_blank">Creative Commons Attribution 3.0.</a></li>
        <li> A model name and description are required. </li>
        <li> Select appropriate category and tags. </li>
        <li> Select a tarball (.tar.gz file) created by <b>gzprop</b>
        <ul>
          <li> Gazebo must be <a href="http://gazebosim.org/wiki/install">installed</a> on your personal computer.</li>
          <li> Run <b>gzprop &lt;model_directory&gt;</b> to generate a tarball for upload.</li>
          <li> For help, run <b>man gzprop</b> in a terminal.</li>
        </ul>
      </ul>

      </div>
    </div>
    </div>
  </div>
